36|47|When they are told, ‘Spend out of what Allah has provided you,’ the faithless say to the faithful, ‘Shall we feed [someone] whom Allah would feed, if He wished? You are only in manifest error.’
36|48|And they say, ‘When will this promise be fulfilled, should you be truthful?’
36|49|They do not await but a single Cry that will seize them as they wrangle.
